Agbar May Sell Bristol Water, Advised by Citigroup, FT Says

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-06-08T22:46:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-08/agbar-may-sell-bristol-water-advised-by-citigroup-ft-says.html
Sociedad General de Aguas de
Barcelona SA, the owner of Bristol Water Group Plc, has
appointed  Citigroup Inc. (C)  to consult on a possible sale of the
utility that it bought five years ago for 362 million pounds
($594 million), including debt, the Financial Times reported,
citing people familiar with the matter.  Agbar, the Spanish water specialist majority-owned by Suez
Environnment SA, could get about 370 million pounds for the U.K.
water supplier, the FT said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 